    <title class="- topic/title ">Prerequisites</title>
    <body>
        <div id="tcc-vtune-prerequisites"/>
        <div id="prerequisites">
            <p>You will need a host system and target system that meet the following
            specifications.</p>
            <table>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colwidth="50"></colspec>
                    <colspec colwidth="50"></colspec>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <p>Device</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <p>Specification</p>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <p>Host System</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <p>In order for the provided script to build the custom Yocto
                                Project*-based image and toolchain, you need a Linux* machine that meets the following requirements:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>A <xref scope="external" format="https" href="https://www.yoctoproject.org/docs/current/ref-manual/ref-manual.html#detailed-supported-distros" class="- topic/xref ">Linux* distribution</xref> that supports Yocto Project.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Internet access.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>A minimum of 500 GB of free disk space.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Recommended: Processor with a minimum of 8 cores.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Recommended: A minimum of 16 GB of RAM.</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>A USB drive to use as a bootable drive. You will use the drive to install the Yocto Project*-based image on the target system. <b>Note:</b> When you create the bootable drive, the existing contents of the drive will be overwritten.</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>A minimum of 64 GB.</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <p>Target system</p>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <p>One of the following boards with the specified processor installed.
                                The processor is denoted by stock keeping unit (SKU).</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Elkhart Lake customer reference board, processor SKU: QTHY or newer</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Tiger Lake UP3 DDR4 customer reference board, processor SKU:
                                        QUYZ or newer</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>Additional hardware:</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Monitor</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Keyboard</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>Mouse</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>(Optional) Ethernet cable to connect the target system to the local
                                        network for remote access</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>The following BIOS versions have been validated to work with Intel® Time Coordinated Computing Tools (Intel® TCC Tools):</p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>For Elkhart Lake customer reference boards:
                                        EHLSFWI1.R00.2091.A00.2002250754</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li>
                                        <p>For Tiger Lake UP3 customer reference boards:
                                        TGLIFUI1.R00.3243.A04.2006302148</p>
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <note>
                <p>To acquire boards or BIOS binaries, contact your Intel representative.</p>
            </note>
        </div>
    </body>
